## Comparative Overview of CBDC Pros and Cons

| Aspect                        | Pros                                                        | Cons                                                         |
|-------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Payment Efficiency**         | Faster, cheaper, real-time payments                          | Infrastructure demands, technological risks                  |
| **Financial Inclusion**        | Access for unbanked, lower costs                             | Digital divide, identity requirements, last-mile challenges  |
| **Monetary Policy**            | New tools (negative rates, helicopter drops)                | Uncertain impact, potential disruption to bank lending       |
| **Financial Stability**        | Risk-free alternative to deposits, reduces moral hazard     | Possible bank disintermediation, increased run risks         |
| **Privacy**                    | Potential for controlled anonymity                           | Risk of surveillance and loss of privacy                      |
| **Competition and Innovation**| Breaks bank/payment provider dominance                       | May crowd out private sector innovation                       |
| **Cost**                      | Reduced cash handling and production costs                   | Distribution and compliance costs remain                      |

