## International Experience and Projects

Several countries have piloted or implemented CBDCs with varying approaches:

- **China**: The Digital Currency Electronic Payment (DCEP) project is one of the largest CBDC initiatives, with extensive trials in major cities ([Kim, 2021](https://www.cnbc.com/video/2021/03/02/why-central-banks-around-the-world-want-to-get-into-digital-currencies.html)).

- **Sweden**: The e-krona project addresses declining cash use with a non-DLT digital currency accessible 24/7 ([Geroni, 2021](https://101blockchains.com/pros-and-cons-of-central-bank-digital-currency/)).

- **Canada and Singapore**: Collaborative projects (Project Jasper and Project Ubin) explore DLT for payments and settlements ([Geroni, 2021](https://101blockchains.com/pros-and-cons-of-central-bank-digital-currency/)).

- **United States**: The Federal Reserve is researching a digital dollar but remains cautious about risks and unclear benefits ([Waller, 2021](https://voxeu.org/article/central-bank-digital-currency-considerations-projects-outlook)).

